04:27:31.760 --> 04:27:37.040
[Guest]: we have been given. So, guaranteed first by writing them into the constitution and secondly

04:27:37.040 --> 04:27:42.000
[Guest]: by reading them into the constitution through the judicial process and if you actually go to

04:27:42.000 --> 04:27:46.800
[Guest]: seek relief and under many of them you may be surprised that I mean it's not so easy to get

04:27:46.800 --> 04:27:54.640
[Guest]: relief. You know actually actual I mean de facto protections are not what is written and there are

04:27:54.640 --> 04:28:00.800
[Guest]: political and governance reasons for those which we can discuss. The other is on the economic

04:28:00.800 --> 04:28:06.240
[Guest]: regulation side. There's quite a bit of work done on economies that are governed by rules and

04:28:06.240 --> 04:28:11.760
[Guest]: economies that are governed by deals where basically they compare the de jure expectation

04:28:11.760 --> 04:28:17.520
[Guest]: of what would happen if the laws were implemented and de facto what actually happens and they say

04:28:17.520 --> 04:28:22.720
[Guest]: there is no correspondence at all like we spend so much time worrying about ease of doing business

04:28:22.720 --> 04:28:27.760
[Guest]: which is basically a measure of de jure requirements but same word bank when it did

04:28:27.760 --> 04:28:33.040
[Guest]: surveys it found reality is very different. So, the construction permit de jure it's supposed

04:28:33.040 --> 04:28:37.680
[Guest]: to take 150 days de facto it takes 30 days. People who actually do the construction say

04:28:37.680 --> 04:28:43.840
[Guest]: I only got the I got the permits in 30 days. How? Because some shortcuts were found or some

04:28:43.840 --> 04:28:48.000
[Guest]: pragmatic decisions were taken on the ground and by the frontline bureaucracy and they were they

04:28:48.000 --> 04:28:52.480
[Guest]: had some incentives maybe there was some corruption maybe not who knows but they got it and it's not

04:28:52.480 --> 04:28:57.840
[Guest]: just of India lots of the researchers who work on this and we show that this is a very common

04:28:57.840 --> 04:29:03.440
[Guest]: phenomenon in developing worlds. As you go to developed world this this gap narrows between

04:29:03.440 --> 04:29:07.760
[Guest]: de jure and de facto. There also there can be some gaps but the gap in developing country is

04:29:07.760 --> 04:29:12.080
[Guest]: very significant. It's the law will say one thing and the reality will be very different. So,

04:29:12.080 --> 04:29:18.880
[Guest]: these two examples are there and I mean they can think about any aspect of state action like one

04:29:18.880 --> 04:29:23.840
[Guest]: of the things about security we are talking about utilitarianism and rights and are we sure that

04:29:23.840 --> 04:29:29.680
