[Amit Varma]: code and this was of course written in 88 and as it happens we turned around we have a broad

05:13:28.400 --> 05:13:34.000
[Amit Varma]: mota mota sense of what we needed to do differently because we did a lot of it it worked for us some

05:13:34.000 --> 05:13:39.600
[Amit Varma]: of that momentum has gone i've had episodes with people like puja mera and our mutual friend the

05:13:39.600 --> 05:13:44.960
[Amit Varma]: wonderful ajay shah and shruti rajgopalan and all that on how we had this golden period between 91

05:13:44.960 --> 05:13:53.200
[Amit Varma]: and 2011 and hundreds of millions came out of poverty but a lot of that has reversed slowed

05:13:53.200 --> 05:13:59.040
[Amit Varma]: changed and at some level it's also a question of mindsets like something that ajay has said

05:13:59.040 --> 05:14:05.840
[Amit Varma]: in past episodes with me and has made a deep impression on me is that there was a time where

05:14:06.800 --> 05:14:12.560
[Amit Varma]: there was this community of policy makers and change makers within government both bureaucrats

05:14:12.560 --> 05:14:17.920
[Amit Varma]: and sometimes politicians who saw sense in it who wanted change who played for change who knew the

05:14:17.920 --> 05:14:24.560
[Amit Varma]: game who knew the direction and his lament was that they may be dying out that within the government

05:14:24.560 --> 05:14:30.800
[Amit Varma]: there may not be so many people in policy who are thinking in those sort of ways and looking ahead

05:14:30.800 --> 05:14:38.160
[Amit Varma]: and also another lament that he had is that many of our finest minds are in economics are actually

05:14:38.160 --> 05:14:43.520
[Amit Varma]: involved in playing the academic circle game my words not his but this is broadly the sense of it

05:14:43.520 --> 05:14:49.200
[Guest]: are involved in playing the academic circles again which which entirely loses connection with

05:14:49.200 --> 05:14:55.600
[Amit Varma]: the real world right so so so what is your sense on kind of both of these and these are like two

