[Guest]: any structural kind of bias that are going for certain kind of people are not able to participate

05:47:00.480 --> 05:47:05.600
[Guest]: in the process that obviously we all care about because in that sense inequality actually harms

05:47:05.600 --> 05:47:11.200
[Guest]: your growth you know exactly that's a different kind of analysis you know and but that's not

05:47:11.200 --> 05:47:16.880
[Guest]: that analysis doesn't need to critique the entire growth episode that we have had and it was the

05:47:16.880 --> 05:47:21.600
[Guest]: kind of growth episode we actually competed with the world right we look at our export growth you

05:47:21.600 --> 05:47:29.440
[Guest]: know our export as a percent of GDP in 1990 was about the same as it was in 1950 and it just

05:47:30.720 --> 05:47:36.720
[Guest]: increased very rapidly after that even then we are a very small part of the world trade we have a

05:47:36.720 --> 05:47:41.840
