05:47:41.840 --> 05:47:45.840
[Guest]: complex products that we make and export we can make more complex products which are more valuable

05:47:45.840 --> 05:47:51.600
[Guest]: and give more GDP we can more more kind of products to export so export can be a major driver of

05:47:51.600 --> 05:47:55.120
[Guest]: Indian growth there's no doubt we are punching way below our weight two percent of the world

05:47:55.120 --> 05:48:00.240
[Guest]: trade is not where we should be you know much higher in terms of GDP you know in the world

05:48:00.240 --> 05:48:05.040
[Guest]: but in trade share is much smaller we should be able to do much more we need to create conditions

05:48:05.040 --> 05:48:09.920
[Guest]: for more private investment and that I think is a sure shot I mean more or less sure shot way to

05:48:09.920 --> 05:48:14.480
[Guest]: you know at least for a decade or so we need to worry I mean there will be a situation in which

05:48:14.480 --> 05:48:19.840
[Guest]: we need to worry too much much more on domestic consumption and all of that worry but my judgment

05:48:19.840 --> 05:48:24.320
[Guest]: of this situation is we are not there yet we need to get more can continue the accumulation stage

05:48:24.320 --> 05:48:29.520
[Guest]: and then we can say okay distribution and all the issues become very important also see for our

05:48:29.520 --> 05:48:36.800
[Guest]: level of income we tax more of the GDP than most countries did at this level of income or we borrow

05:48:36.800 --> 05:48:41.280
[Guest]: more as percent of GDP than most of our comparable countries so it's not like the state is not taxing

05:48:41.280 --> 05:48:47.760
[Guest]: and borrowing and we can talk about how to tax better and borrow better maybe we can do less

05:48:47.760 --> 05:48:53.120
[Guest]: financial depression on the borrowing side we can have more efficient tax system on the expenditure

05:48:53.120 --> 05:48:56.640
[Guest]: side we can talk about better allocative and operational efficiency as a democracy we can

05:48:56.640 --> 05:49:00.080
[Guest]: debate what is worth spending on how to spend on it all those are very important conversation

05:49:00.640 --> 05:49:06.880
[Guest]: but if anybody argues that we should be taxing more and borrowing more at level of GDP the onus

05:49:06.880 --> 05:49:12.880
[Guest]: is on them to prove why why it can be done well because I am showing you I mean evidence I mean

05:49:12.880 --> 05:49:19.840
[Guest]: very clear evidence that we are actually taxing pretty large part of the GDP larger than we should

05:49:19.840 --> 05:49:25.600
[Guest]: at this I mean we usually continue at this level of development so all those are myths obviously but

05:49:25.600 --> 05:49:30.080
[Guest]: so without growth how are you going to even deliver on the all the good stuff that you want

05:49:30.080 --> 05:49:35.760
[Guest]: to you know redistribute and do more for people you know so I think there is a and we could do

05:49:35.760 --> 05:49:41.040
[Guest]: so much more when since we started growing we could do more of subsidies and welfare schemes

05:49:41.040 --> 05:49:45.440
[Guest]: and all there is a lot of critique on how it was done how much of it went to middle class and all

05:49:45.440 --> 05:49:49.440
[Guest]: of that I completely agree with that I've said that's what I should study also so all that is

05:49:49.440 --> 05:49:54.000
[Guest]: there but I'm telling you it's a very small part of the problem much bigger problem is to how to

05:49:54.000 --> 05:50:00.880
[Amit Varma]: get to that twenty thousand dollar GDP at least per capita I think without growth we are like

