05:53:07.120 --> 05:53:11.840
[Guest]: but the fact of the matter that they have a voice and they can make things difficult and they have a

05:53:11.840 --> 05:53:17.280
[Guest]: right to make it difficult for you and therefore finding bargains whether it's in agriculture

05:53:17.280 --> 05:53:23.600
[Guest]: whether it's in labor whether it's in land markets and all which make the reform more sustainable

05:53:23.600 --> 05:53:30.400
[Guest]: is should be the focus of the reformist when reform minded thinkers and civil servants and

05:53:30.400 --> 05:53:35.040
[Guest]: all of that and I think we are seeing some of that I mean not as much as would be good

05:53:35.040 --> 05:53:40.480
[Guest]: but we are seeing some of that and also continuing the strengths of our democracy we should harness

05:53:40.480 --> 05:53:44.560
[Guest]: the strength of our democracy now all of these points I made is working towards this one point

05:53:45.280 --> 05:53:52.960
[Guest]: which is that we got rapid growth in a coalition era with all kind of arrogant independent

05:53:52.960 --> 05:53:57.840
[Guest]: institutions saying whatever they wanted to say a press which made the life of government very

05:53:57.840 --> 05:54:04.480
[Guest]: very difficult often challenging it weak governments which with minority I mean leading parties

05:54:04.480 --> 05:54:10.080
[Guest]: and necessity of coalition even smallest party could basically make the government fall and we

05:54:10.080 --> 05:54:15.120
[Guest]: got really rapid growth I mean for it especially for democracy but even generally we were among

05:54:15.120 --> 05:54:19.600
[Guest]: the fastest growing economies in the world the second fastest growing large economy in the world

05:54:19.600 --> 05:54:24.880
[Guest]: for a very long time while having those kind of institutional settings and that kind of a

05:54:24.880 --> 05:54:30.720
[Guest]: democratic setup so we should harness those you know we should harness those very carefully and

05:54:30.720 --> 05:54:35.760
[Guest]: see how we got that growth so most important thing to learn from our own past experience

05:54:35.760 --> 05:54:42.800
[Guest]: is good to look at Korea and China and all of that for some purposes but our own past is very

05:54:42.800 --> 05:54:48.160
[Guest]: instructive there's a lot to learn from there how it worked what worked we may not replicate what we

05:54:48.160 --> 05:54:52.880
[Guest]: did that's not going to work now the economy has changed the world has changed but at a meta level

05:54:52.880 --> 05:54:57.680
[Guest]: there's a lot of insight on how we harness our democratic institutions and our democratic

